whatever written in search box is called 'query'.

Splunk uses SPL i.e. splunk search proceessing language


META DATA:
Meta data is the information about a data.
Host: Ip from where the data generated
Source: actual path of the data

Sourcetype: Logical segregation of data.
Say if you are using google chrome, history ralate data is different from your download related date, that is a kind of logical segregation.



Splunk uses pipeline concept. i.e. output of before pipe will be the input for after pipe.

